result.execSummary:
The defendant Jerry L Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Escape-Juvenile Criminal Arrest, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.42(3)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jerry L Anderson in court, in custody, with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.   Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts #2, 3 and 4 are read into Count #1.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

5  YEARS IMPRISONMENT.
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Any other term deemed appropriate by agent. 
*No contact with:   General Refrigeration. 
*Perform 100 Hours Community Service.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 7 MONTHS non working hours (apply 132 Days Credit) to begin forthwith..  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is  not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
